title: Google\Cloud\Kms\V1\CryptoKeyVersion
name: CryptoKeyVersion
description:
A [CryptoKeyVersion][google.cloud.kms.v1.CryptoKeyVersion] represents an individual cryptographic key, and the associated key material.

It can be used for cryptographic operations either directly, or via its parent [CryptoKey][google.cloud.kms.v1.CryptoKey], in which case the server will choose the appropriate version for the operation. For security reasons, the raw cryptographic key material represented by a [CryptoKeyVersion][google.cloud.kms.v1.CryptoKeyVersion] can never be viewed or exported. It can only be used to encrypt or decrypt data when an authorized user or application invokes Cloud KMS.
